{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012q9xj7KPtJBNnkjPYMMYq8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary document.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis: Ralph-Burning-Rewrite Project\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the project, here's what has been built across 6 completed loops:\n\n### **PROJECT OVERVIEW**\nThis is a Rust-based automation orchestration engine (`ralph-burning`) implementing a multi-stage workflow system with support for multiple flow presets, backend diversity, stage contract validation, and project/run management.\n\n**Cargo.toml Dependencies:**\n- Async runtime: `tokio` (multi-threaded with sync/time features)\n- CLI: `clap` (4.5 with derive)\n- Serialization: `serde`, `serde_json`, `toml`, `toml_edit`\n- JSON Schema: `schemars` (0.8) for contract payload validation\n- Error handling: `thiserror` (2)\n- Time: `chrono` (with clock and serde features)\n- Logging: `tracing` + `tracing-subscriber`\n\n---\n\n### **LOOP 1-4 DELIVERABLES (Foundation + Governance + Contracts)**\n\n**Loop 1: Domain Model & Workspace Init**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs`\n- Defined core types: `StageId` (16 enum variants), `FlowPreset` (4 variants: Standard, QuickDev, DocsChange, CiImprovement)\n- `StageCursor` tracking: cycle, attempt, completion_round, stage position\n- `ProjectId`, `RunId` newtypes with validation\n- Failure classes enum: `TransportFailure`, `SchemaValidationFailure`, `DomainValidationFailure`, `Timeout`, `Cancellation`, `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n**Loop 2: Stage Contract Registry & Deterministic Validation**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs`\n- Three contract families: `Planning`, `Execution`, `Validation`\n- `StageContract` binds StageId to payload family, schema, semantic rules, and renderer\n- Contract evaluation pipeline: schema validation → semantic validation → outcome check → rendering\n- Returns `ValidatedBundle` (payload + rendered artifact) on success\n- Maps all failures to appropriate `FailureClass`\n\n**Loop 3: Workspace Governance & Config**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/`\n- `WorkspaceConfig` with version tracking (current: 1)\n- `WorkspaceSettings`: prompt_review.enabled flag, default_flow, default_backend, default_model\n- Active project tracking via `.ralph-burning/active-project` file\n- Configuration precedence chain for backend selection\n\n**Loop 4: Project & Run Record Foundation**\n- **Files:**\n  - `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs`\n  - `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs`\n  - `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs`\n\n**Canonical Run State (run.json):**\n- `RunSnapshot`: active_run, status, cycle_history, completion_rounds, rollback_point_meta, amendment_queue, status_summary\n- `RunStatus` enum: NotStarted, Running, Paused, Completed, Failed\n- `ActiveRun`: run_id, stage_cursor, started_at\n- Semantic validation: ensures status/active_run consistency\n\n**Journal System (journal.ndjson):**\n- NDJSON format with monotonic sequence numbering\n- `JournalEvent` structure: sequence, timestamp, event_type, details\n- `JournalEventType`: ProjectCreated, RunStarted, StageEntered, StageCompleted, CycleAdvanced, CompletionRoundAdvanced, RunCompleted, RunFailed, RollbackCreated, AmendmentQueued\n- Lifecycle event builders: `run_started_event()`, `stage_entered_event()`, `stage_completed_event()`, etc.\n- Journal integrity validation: first event must be project_created with sequence 1\n\n**Durable History:**\n- `PayloadRecord`: payload_id, stage_id, cycle, attempt, created_at, typed payload JSON\n- `ArtifactRecord`: artifact_id, payload_id, stage_id, created_at, markdown content\n- `RuntimeLogEntry`: timestamp, level (Debug/Info/Warn), source, message\n- Stored separately: `history/payloads/`, `history/artifacts/`, `runtime/logs/`\n\n**Port Definitions:**\n- `ProjectStorePort`: CRUD operations, atomic creation, deletion staging\n- `JournalStorePort`: read_journal, append_event\n- `RunSnapshotPort`/`RunSnapshotWritePort`: snapshot read/write operations\n- `PayloadArtifactWritePort`: write pairs atomically, remove pairs (rollback)\n- `RuntimeLogWritePort`: append-only logging (best-effort, not durable history)\n- `ArtifactStorePort`: list payloads and artifacts\n\n---\n\n### **LOOP 5: AGENT EXECUTION FACADE**\n\n**Backend Selection & Role Mapping**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs`\n\n**Core Types:**\n- `BackendFamily` enum: Claude, Codex, OpenRouter, Stub (with display names, default models, capability metadata)\n- `BackendRole` enum: Planner, Implementer, Reviewer, QaValidator, CompletionJudge\n  - Each role has default backend/model targets\n  - Deterministic stage-to-role mapping: `BackendRole::for_stage(stage_id)`\n  - Session reuse eligibility per role\n- `ResolvedBackendTarget`: combines BackendSpec + ModelSpec\n- `BackendSpec` & `ModelSpec`: includes display name and capabilities metadata\n- `SessionPolicy`: NewSession or ReuseIfAllowed\n\n**Invocation Request/Response**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/model.rs`\n- `InvocationRequest`: invocation_id, project_root, stage_contract, role, resolved_target, payload, timeout, cancellation_token, session_policy, prior_session, attempt_number\n- `InvocationPayload`: prompt string + context JSON\n- `InvocationEnvelope`: raw_output_reference, parsed_payload (JSON), invocation_metadata, timestamp\n- `InvocationMetadata`: invocation_id, duration, token_counts (prompt/completion/total), model used, attempt number\n- `RawOutputReference`: Inline(String) or Stored(PathBuf) for determinism without bloat\n- `CancellationToken`: Arc-based async cancellation with Tokio notification\n\n**Backend Resolution**\n- `BackendResolver` implements precedence chain: explicit override → project config → workspace defaults → role defaults\n- `BackendSelectionConfig` struct for parsing config values\n\n**Execution Port & Service**\n- **Traits:**\n  - `AgentExecutionPort`: async check_capability, check_availability, invoke, cancel\n  - `RawOutputPort`: persist_raw_output to runtime/backend/ directory\n  - `SessionStorePort`: load/save sessions.json per project\n\n- **Service:**\n  - `AgentExecutionService<A, R, S>` generic over adapter, raw output store, session store\n  - Orchestrates: capability check → availability check → session load → invocation → raw output persistence → envelope construction\n  - Failure mapping to FailureClass: transport errors → TransportFailure, malformed → SchemaValidationFailure, domain issues → DomainValidationFailure, deadline → Timeout, cancel → Cancellation\n  - Timeout enforcement via `tokio::select!` with no retries on timeout\n  - Cancellation propagation: signal immediately halts invocation\n\n**Session Management**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/session.rs`\n- `SessionMetadata`: role, backend_family, model_id, session_id, created_at, last_used_at, invocation_count\n- `PersistedSessions`: vector of metadata, serialized to sessions.json per project\n- `SessionManager`: load_reusable_session (checks role/target support), record_session (updates or creates)\n\n**Stub Backend Adapter**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/stub_backend.rs`\n- `StubBackendAdapter`: implements AgentExecutionPort with deterministic canned payloads\n- Builder methods: with_delay, unavailable, without_stage_support, with_invoke_failure\n- Produces valid `InvocationEnvelope` with typed payloads and token counts\n- Session reuse simulation based on role/target eligibility\n- Test-only injectable via environment variables: `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_BACKEND_UNAVAILABLE`, `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_FAIL_INVOKE_STAGE`\n\n---\n\n### **LOOP 6: STANDARD PRESET RUN START ORCHESTRATION**\n\n**Engine Orchestration**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` (586 lines)\n\n**Stage Plan Derivation:**\n- `standard_stage_plan(prompt_review_enabled: bool)` → derives canonical order with optional prompt_review\n- Standard flow stages: PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview\n\n**Preflight Validation:**\n- `resolve_stage_plan()`: resolves backend targets for all stages upfront\n- `preflight_check()`: validates capability and availability for all stages before any mutation\n- If any preflight fails, all canonical state (run.json, journal, payloads, sessions, active-project) remains unchanged\n\n**Run Initialization:**\n- `generate_run_id()`: timestamp-based ID (format: \"run-YYYYMMDDHHMMSS\")\n- Creates initial `RunSnapshot`: status=Running, active_run with first stage, cycle=1, attempt=1, completion_rounds=1\n- Persists run.json BEFORE journal events (atomic boundary)\n- Appends run_started journal event with sequence tracking\n\n**Stage Execution Loop:**\n- **Per stage:**\n  1. Emit stage_entered journal event\n  2. Update snapshot cursor\n  3. Invoke agent_service with payload\n  4. Evaluate contract (schema + domain + outcome + render)\n  5. Persist payload + artifact pair atomically\n  6. Update snapshot cursor to next stage\n  7. Append stage_completed journal event\n  8. Best-effort runtime log append\n\n**Atomic Stage Commit:**\n- **Commit order (critical for durability):**\n  1. Write payload + artifact pair to history/\n  2. Write snapshot with updated cursor\n  3. Append stage_completed journal event\n- **Failure handling:** If any step fails after stage_entered:\n  - Previous steps are rolled back (artifact_write.remove_payload_artifact_pair)\n  - Snapshot reverted to pre-commit state\n  - Run marked failed via fail_run()\n  - No partial durable history visible (stage_completed event only exists if all steps succeed)\n\n**Terminal Conditions:**\n- Any failure halts execution (no retries in this slice)\n- Non-passing QA/review outcomes (RequestChanges/ConditionallyApproved/Rejected) are fatal\n- On straight-through success: status=Completed, active_run=null, run_completed journal event persisted\n\n**CLI Integration**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs`\n- `handle_start()` validates:\n  - Workspace version support\n  - Active project selection\n  - Canonical project record integrity\n  - Flow preset is Standard (other flows fail with UnsupportedFlow error)\n  - Run snapshot status is NotStarted with no active run\n- Wires adapters and calls engine::execute_standard_run\n- Prints success/failure to stdout\n\n**Project Directory Structure**\n- **Required subdirectories (created on project init):**\n  - `history/payloads/` — durable stage output\n  - `history/artifacts/` — durable rendered markdown\n  - `runtime/logs/` — operational logs (best-effort)\n  - `runtime/backend/` — raw backend output (per invocation)\n  - `runtime/temp/` — temporary files during execution\n  - `amendments/` — amendment queue data (future)\n  - `rollback/` — rollback point metadata (future)\n\n---\n\n### **CURRENT STATE: WHAT'S BUILT**\n\n**Fully Implemented & Tested:**\n1. ✓ Workspace initialization and configuration management\n2. ✓ Flow preset definitions (4 flows with deterministic stage sequences)\n3. ✓ Stage contract registry with three payload families\n4. ✓ Schema/semantic validation with deterministic markdown rendering\n5. ✓ Effective config resolution with precedence chain\n6. ✓ Project and run record models with canonical JSON/NDJSON persistence\n7. ✓ Journal system with sequence validation and integrity checks\n8. ✓ Backend family/role/model abstractions\n9. ✓ Agent execution facade with port boundaries\n10. ✓ Cancellation token support with async propagation\n11. ✓ Session management and reuse policy enforcement\n12. ✓ Stub backend adapter with deterministic canned payloads\n13. ✓ Standard flow run orchestration engine\n14. ✓ Atomic stage commit with rollback on failure\n15. ✓ Payload/artifact pair persistence (durable history)\n16. ✓ Journal event sequencing and lifecycle tracking\n17. ✓ Runtime logging (best-effort, separate from durable history)\n18. ✓ Preflight capability/availability checks\n19. ✓ Raw output persistence to runtime/backend/\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/` contains 14 test modules:\n  - agent_execution_test.rs, stub_backend_test.rs\n  - workflow_engine_test.rs\n  - project_run_record_test.rs, journal_test.rs, query_test.rs\n  - stage_contract_test.rs, renderer_test.rs\n  - config_test.rs, workspace_test.rs, domain_test.rs\n  - flow_preset_test.rs, active_project_test.rs, adapter_contract_test.rs\n- CLI integration tests in cli.rs\n\n---\n\n### **WHAT'S NOT YET BUILT (Beyond Loop 6)**\n\nPer the loop 6 spec, deliberately excluded from current implementation:\n1. **No retry/remediation** — any failure halts immediately\n2. **No resume logic** — cannot restart an interrupted run\n3. **No amendment queue behavior** — non-passing QA/review is terminal\n4. **No completion round advancement** — no re-execution cycles\n5. **No non-standard flow support** — only standard flow in run start\n6. **No rollback/restoration** — no rollback point management\n7. **No actual backend adapters** — only stub (deterministic canned responses)\n\n---\n\n### **KEY ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS**\n\n**Port-Driven Design:**\n- All I/O abstracted behind ports (trait boundaries)\n- Tests inject test doubles; CLI wires production adapters\n\n**Atomic Durability:**\n- Run.json is single source of truth for run state\n- Journal.ndjson is append-only event log (immutable history)\n- Stage commit only succeeds if payload, artifact, snapshot, AND journal all persist\n- Failures include rollback to undo partial writes\n\n**Deterministic Evaluation:**\n- Stage contracts define exactly what valid outputs look like\n- Rendering is deterministic (same input → same artifact)\n- No external state during execution (stub backend produces canned payloads)\n\n**Failure Taxonomy:**\n- Each failure class maps to a retry/policy decision (future)\n- Currently: all failures halt the run immediately\n\n**Session Reuse:**\n- Some roles/targets support session continuity (Implementer, Reviewer, QaValidator)\n- Sessions.json tracks per-project backend sessions\n- Policy-driven (NewSession vs ReuseIfAllowed)\n\n---\n\n### **KEY FILES TO UNDERSTAND RETRIES/RESUME/PROMPT-REVIEW**\n\nCurrently **not implemented** but architecture prepared for:\n\n1. **Retry Logic:** Would be in an orchestration layer above engine.rs\n   - Failure class determines retry eligibility\n   - Loop back to stage invocation, increment attempt counter\n   - Respect cycle boundaries\n\n2. **Resume Logic:** Would extend execute_standard_run\n   - Read current snapshot and journal\n   - Skip already-completed stages\n   - Resume from active stage cursor\n\n3. **Prompt Review Stage:** Already defined in contracts/payloads\n   - Falls under Planning contract family\n   - Standard flow includes it (can be disabled via prompt_review.enabled)\n   - No special handling yet (treated like any other stage)\n\n4. **Amendment Queue:** Data structures exist in run.json\n   - `AmendmentQueueState`: pending array + processed_count\n   - No implementation for queueing or processing\n\n---\n\n### **DEPENDENCY GRAPH (LOOP SEQUENCING)**\n\n- Loop 1 (Domain) → independent foundation\n- Loop 2 (Contracts) → depends on Loop 1\n- Loop 3 (Workspace Governance) → depends on Loop 1\n- Loop 4 (Project/Run Records) → depends on Loops 1, 2, 3\n- Loop 5 (Agent Execution) → depends on Loops 1, 2, 3, 4\n- Loop 6 (Run Orchestration) → depends on Loops 1-5\n\n**Next logical loops (roadmap):**\n- Loop 7: Retry/remediation with failure class semantics\n- Loop 8: Resume capability\n- Loop 9: Amendment queue and completion round behavior\n- Loop 10+: Non-standard flow support, rollback, etc.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a **well-architected, production-grade workflow engine foundation**. The codebase demonstrates:\n- Clear separation of concerns (domain, ports, adapters, CLI)\n- Comprehensive error handling with semantic failure classes\n- Atomic durability guarantees for critical state\n- Extensibility through port-based design\n- Full test coverage for implemented features\n- Deterministic, testable behavior (via stub backend)\n\nThe implementation is **ready for the next layer: retry/remediation logic** which would consume the failure classes and orchestrate re-execution of failed stages."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a852055c33d6a62dc (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 72292\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 99090</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04681ab0-f55e-4c96-b8ca-61b2a1e590bf","uuid":"9b011d25-02e4-4b42-b23c-3546d2f28d83","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand what has been built in this Rust project across 6 completed loops. Please do the following:\n\n1. Read the specs for loops 5 and 6 (they are the most recent and relevant):\n   - Find and read the spec files under loops/005-* and loops/006-*\n   \n2. Look at the current source code structure under ralph-burning-rewrite/src/ - list all files and read key files to understand what's implemented.\n\n3. Specifically look for:\n   - What retry/failure handling exists currently\n   - What resume logic exists\n   - What prompt review stage logic exists\n   - The orchestration engine / run executor code\n   - The stage contracts that are defined\n   - The error types and failure classes defined\n\n4. Read the Cargo.toml to understand dependencies\n\nBe very thorough - I need a comprehensive picture of the current codebase state.","agentId":"a852055c33d6a62dc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary document.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis: Ralph-Burning-Rewrite Project\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the project, here's what has been built across 6 completed loops:\n\n### **PROJECT OVERVIEW**\nThis is a Rust-based automation orchestration engine (`ralph-burning`) implementing a multi-stage workflow system with support for multiple flow presets, backend diversity, stage contract validation, and project/run management.\n\n**Cargo.toml Dependencies:**\n- Async runtime: `tokio` (multi-threaded with sync/time features)\n- CLI: `clap` (4.5 with derive)\n- Serialization: `serde`, `serde_json`, `toml`, `toml_edit`\n- JSON Schema: `schemars` (0.8) for contract payload validation\n- Error handling: `thiserror` (2)\n- Time: `chrono` (with clock and serde features)\n- Logging: `tracing` + `tracing-subscriber`\n\n---\n\n### **LOOP 1-4 DELIVERABLES (Foundation + Governance + Contracts)**\n\n**Loop 1: Domain Model & Workspace Init**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs`\n- Defined core types: `StageId` (16 enum variants), `FlowPreset` (4 variants: Standard, QuickDev, DocsChange, CiImprovement)\n- `StageCursor` tracking: cycle, attempt, completion_round, stage position\n- `ProjectId`, `RunId` newtypes with validation\n- Failure classes enum: `TransportFailure`, `SchemaValidationFailure`, `DomainValidationFailure`, `Timeout`, `Cancellation`, `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n**Loop 2: Stage Contract Registry & Deterministic Validation**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs`\n- Three contract families: `Planning`, `Execution`, `Validation`\n- `StageContract` binds StageId to payload family, schema, semantic rules, and renderer\n- Contract evaluation pipeline: schema validation → semantic validation → outcome check → rendering\n- Returns `ValidatedBundle` (payload + rendered artifact) on success\n- Maps all failures to appropriate `FailureClass`\n\n**Loop 3: Workspace Governance & Config**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/`\n- `WorkspaceConfig` with version tracking (current: 1)\n- `WorkspaceSettings`: prompt_review.enabled flag, default_flow, default_backend, default_model\n- Active project tracking via `.ralph-burning/active-project` file\n- Configuration precedence chain for backend selection\n\n**Loop 4: Project & Run Record Foundation**\n- **Files:**\n  - `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs`\n  - `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs`\n  - `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs`\n\n**Canonical Run State (run.json):**\n- `RunSnapshot`: active_run, status, cycle_history, completion_rounds, rollback_point_meta, amendment_queue, status_summary\n- `RunStatus` enum: NotStarted, Running, Paused, Completed, Failed\n- `ActiveRun`: run_id, stage_cursor, started_at\n- Semantic validation: ensures status/active_run consistency\n\n**Journal System (journal.ndjson):**\n- NDJSON format with monotonic sequence numbering\n- `JournalEvent` structure: sequence, timestamp, event_type, details\n- `JournalEventType`: ProjectCreated, RunStarted, StageEntered, StageCompleted, CycleAdvanced, CompletionRoundAdvanced, RunCompleted, RunFailed, RollbackCreated, AmendmentQueued\n- Lifecycle event builders: `run_started_event()`, `stage_entered_event()`, `stage_completed_event()`, etc.\n- Journal integrity validation: first event must be project_created with sequence 1\n\n**Durable History:**\n- `PayloadRecord`: payload_id, stage_id, cycle, attempt, created_at, typed payload JSON\n- `ArtifactRecord`: artifact_id, payload_id, stage_id, created_at, markdown content\n- `RuntimeLogEntry`: timestamp, level (Debug/Info/Warn), source, message\n- Stored separately: `history/payloads/`, `history/artifacts/`, `runtime/logs/`\n\n**Port Definitions:**\n- `ProjectStorePort`: CRUD operations, atomic creation, deletion staging\n- `JournalStorePort`: read_journal, append_event\n- `RunSnapshotPort`/`RunSnapshotWritePort`: snapshot read/write operations\n- `PayloadArtifactWritePort`: write pairs atomically, remove pairs (rollback)\n- `RuntimeLogWritePort`: append-only logging (best-effort, not durable history)\n- `ArtifactStorePort`: list payloads and artifacts\n\n---\n\n### **LOOP 5: AGENT EXECUTION FACADE**\n\n**Backend Selection & Role Mapping**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs`\n\n**Core Types:**\n- `BackendFamily` enum: Claude, Codex, OpenRouter, Stub (with display names, default models, capability metadata)\n- `BackendRole` enum: Planner, Implementer, Reviewer, QaValidator, CompletionJudge\n  - Each role has default backend/model targets\n  - Deterministic stage-to-role mapping: `BackendRole::for_stage(stage_id)`\n  - Session reuse eligibility per role\n- `ResolvedBackendTarget`: combines BackendSpec + ModelSpec\n- `BackendSpec` & `ModelSpec`: includes display name and capabilities metadata\n- `SessionPolicy`: NewSession or ReuseIfAllowed\n\n**Invocation Request/Response**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/model.rs`\n- `InvocationRequest`: invocation_id, project_root, stage_contract, role, resolved_target, payload, timeout, cancellation_token, session_policy, prior_session, attempt_number\n- `InvocationPayload`: prompt string + context JSON\n- `InvocationEnvelope`: raw_output_reference, parsed_payload (JSON), invocation_metadata, timestamp\n- `InvocationMetadata`: invocation_id, duration, token_counts (prompt/completion/total), model used, attempt number\n- `RawOutputReference`: Inline(String) or Stored(PathBuf) for determinism without bloat\n- `CancellationToken`: Arc-based async cancellation with Tokio notification\n\n**Backend Resolution**\n- `BackendResolver` implements precedence chain: explicit override → project config → workspace defaults → role defaults\n- `BackendSelectionConfig` struct for parsing config values\n\n**Execution Port & Service**\n- **Traits:**\n  - `AgentExecutionPort`: async check_capability, check_availability, invoke, cancel\n  - `RawOutputPort`: persist_raw_output to runtime/backend/ directory\n  - `SessionStorePort`: load/save sessions.json per project\n\n- **Service:**\n  - `AgentExecutionService<A, R, S>` generic over adapter, raw output store, session store\n  - Orchestrates: capability check → availability check → session load → invocation → raw output persistence → envelope construction\n  - Failure mapping to FailureClass: transport errors → TransportFailure, malformed → SchemaValidationFailure, domain issues → DomainValidationFailure, deadline → Timeout, cancel → Cancellation\n  - Timeout enforcement via `tokio::select!` with no retries on timeout\n  - Cancellation propagation: signal immediately halts invocation\n\n**Session Management**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/session.rs`\n- `SessionMetadata`: role, backend_family, model_id, session_id, created_at, last_used_at, invocation_count\n- `PersistedSessions`: vector of metadata, serialized to sessions.json per project\n- `SessionManager`: load_reusable_session (checks role/target support), record_session (updates or creates)\n\n**Stub Backend Adapter**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/stub_backend.rs`\n- `StubBackendAdapter`: implements AgentExecutionPort with deterministic canned payloads\n- Builder methods: with_delay, unavailable, without_stage_support, with_invoke_failure\n- Produces valid `InvocationEnvelope` with typed payloads and token counts\n- Session reuse simulation based on role/target eligibility\n- Test-only injectable via environment variables: `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_BACKEND_UNAVAILABLE`, `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_FAIL_INVOKE_STAGE`\n\n---\n\n### **LOOP 6: STANDARD PRESET RUN START ORCHESTRATION**\n\n**Engine Orchestration**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` (586 lines)\n\n**Stage Plan Derivation:**\n- `standard_stage_plan(prompt_review_enabled: bool)` → derives canonical order with optional prompt_review\n- Standard flow stages: PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview\n\n**Preflight Validation:**\n- `resolve_stage_plan()`: resolves backend targets for all stages upfront\n- `preflight_check()`: validates capability and availability for all stages before any mutation\n- If any preflight fails, all canonical state (run.json, journal, payloads, sessions, active-project) remains unchanged\n\n**Run Initialization:**\n- `generate_run_id()`: timestamp-based ID (format: \"run-YYYYMMDDHHMMSS\")\n- Creates initial `RunSnapshot`: status=Running, active_run with first stage, cycle=1, attempt=1, completion_rounds=1\n- Persists run.json BEFORE journal events (atomic boundary)\n- Appends run_started journal event with sequence tracking\n\n**Stage Execution Loop:**\n- **Per stage:**\n  1. Emit stage_entered journal event\n  2. Update snapshot cursor\n  3. Invoke agent_service with payload\n  4. Evaluate contract (schema + domain + outcome + render)\n  5. Persist payload + artifact pair atomically\n  6. Update snapshot cursor to next stage\n  7. Append stage_completed journal event\n  8. Best-effort runtime log append\n\n**Atomic Stage Commit:**\n- **Commit order (critical for durability):**\n  1. Write payload + artifact pair to history/\n  2. Write snapshot with updated cursor\n  3. Append stage_completed journal event\n- **Failure handling:** If any step fails after stage_entered:\n  - Previous steps are rolled back (artifact_write.remove_payload_artifact_pair)\n  - Snapshot reverted to pre-commit state\n  - Run marked failed via fail_run()\n  - No partial durable history visible (stage_completed event only exists if all steps succeed)\n\n**Terminal Conditions:**\n- Any failure halts execution (no retries in this slice)\n- Non-passing QA/review outcomes (RequestChanges/ConditionallyApproved/Rejected) are fatal\n- On straight-through success: status=Completed, active_run=null, run_completed journal event persisted\n\n**CLI Integration**\n- **File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs`\n- `handle_start()` validates:\n  - Workspace version support\n  - Active project selection\n  - Canonical project record integrity\n  - Flow preset is Standard (other flows fail with UnsupportedFlow error)\n  - Run snapshot status is NotStarted with no active run\n- Wires adapters and calls engine::execute_standard_run\n- Prints success/failure to stdout\n\n**Project Directory Structure**\n- **Required subdirectories (created on project init):**\n  - `history/payloads/` — durable stage output\n  - `history/artifacts/` — durable rendered markdown\n  - `runtime/logs/` — operational logs (best-effort)\n  - `runtime/backend/` — raw backend output (per invocation)\n  - `runtime/temp/` — temporary files during execution\n  - `amendments/` — amendment queue data (future)\n  - `rollback/` — rollback point metadata (future)\n\n---\n\n### **CURRENT STATE: WHAT'S BUILT**\n\n**Fully Implemented & Tested:**\n1. ✓ Workspace initialization and configuration management\n2. ✓ Flow preset definitions (4 flows with deterministic stage sequences)\n3. ✓ Stage contract registry with three payload families\n4. ✓ Schema/semantic validation with deterministic markdown rendering\n5. ✓ Effective config resolution with precedence chain\n6. ✓ Project and run record models with canonical JSON/NDJSON persistence\n7. ✓ Journal system with sequence validation and integrity checks\n8. ✓ Backend family/role/model abstractions\n9. ✓ Agent execution facade with port boundaries\n10. ✓ Cancellation token support with async propagation\n11. ✓ Session management and reuse policy enforcement\n12. ✓ Stub backend adapter with deterministic canned payloads\n13. ✓ Standard flow run orchestration engine\n14. ✓ Atomic stage commit with rollback on failure\n15. ✓ Payload/artifact pair persistence (durable history)\n16. ✓ Journal event sequencing and lifecycle tracking\n17. ✓ Runtime logging (best-effort, separate from durable history)\n18. ✓ Preflight capability/availability checks\n19. ✓ Raw output persistence to runtime/backend/\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/` contains 14 test modules:\n  - agent_execution_test.rs, stub_backend_test.rs\n  - workflow_engine_test.rs\n  - project_run_record_test.rs, journal_test.rs, query_test.rs\n  - stage_contract_test.rs, renderer_test.rs\n  - config_test.rs, workspace_test.rs, domain_test.rs\n  - flow_preset_test.rs, active_project_test.rs, adapter_contract_test.rs\n- CLI integration tests in cli.rs\n\n---\n\n### **WHAT'S NOT YET BUILT (Beyond Loop 6)**\n\nPer the loop 6 spec, deliberately excluded from current implementation:\n1. **No retry/remediation** — any failure halts immediately\n2. **No resume logic** — cannot restart an interrupted run\n3. **No amendment queue behavior** — non-passing QA/review is terminal\n4. **No completion round advancement** — no re-execution cycles\n5. **No non-standard flow support** — only standard flow in run start\n6. **No rollback/restoration** — no rollback point management\n7. **No actual backend adapters** — only stub (deterministic canned responses)\n\n---\n\n### **KEY ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS**\n\n**Port-Driven Design:**\n- All I/O abstracted behind ports (trait boundaries)\n- Tests inject test doubles; CLI wires production adapters\n\n**Atomic Durability:**\n- Run.json is single source of truth for run state\n- Journal.ndjson is append-only event log (immutable history)\n- Stage commit only succeeds if payload, artifact, snapshot, AND journal all persist\n- Failures include rollback to undo partial writes\n\n**Deterministic Evaluation:**\n- Stage contracts define exactly what valid outputs look like\n- Rendering is deterministic (same input → same artifact)\n- No external state during execution (stub backend produces canned payloads)\n\n**Failure Taxonomy:**\n- Each failure class maps to a retry/policy decision (future)\n- Currently: all failures halt the run immediately\n\n**Session Reuse:**\n- Some roles/targets support session continuity (Implementer, Reviewer, QaValidator)\n- Sessions.json tracks per-project backend sessions\n- Policy-driven (NewSession vs ReuseIfAllowed)\n\n---\n\n### **KEY FILES TO UNDERSTAND RETRIES/RESUME/PROMPT-REVIEW**\n\nCurrently **not implemented** but architecture prepared for:\n\n1. **Retry Logic:** Would be in an orchestration layer above engine.rs\n   - Failure class determines retry eligibility\n   - Loop back to stage invocation, increment attempt counter\n   - Respect cycle boundaries\n\n2. **Resume Logic:** Would extend execute_standard_run\n   - Read current snapshot and journal\n   - Skip already-completed stages\n   - Resume from active stage cursor\n\n3. **Prompt Review Stage:** Already defined in contracts/payloads\n   - Falls under Planning contract family\n   - Standard flow includes it (can be disabled via prompt_review.enabled)\n   - No special handling yet (treated like any other stage)\n\n4. **Amendment Queue:** Data structures exist in run.json\n   - `AmendmentQueueState`: pending array + processed_count\n   - No implementation for queueing or processing\n\n---\n\n### **DEPENDENCY GRAPH (LOOP SEQUENCING)**\n\n- Loop 1 (Domain) → independent foundation\n- Loop 2 (Contracts) → depends on Loop 1\n- Loop 3 (Workspace Governance) → depends on Loop 1\n- Loop 4 (Project/Run Records) → depends on Loops 1, 2, 3\n- Loop 5 (Agent Execution) → depends on Loops 1, 2, 3, 4\n- Loop 6 (Run Orchestration) → depends on Loops 1-5\n\n**Next logical loops (roadmap):**\n- Loop 7: Retry/remediation with failure class semantics\n- Loop 8: Resume capability\n- Loop 9: Amendment queue and completion round behavior\n- Loop 10+: Non-standard flow support, rollback, etc.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a **well-architected, production-grade workflow engine foundation**. The codebase demonstrates:\n- Clear separation of concerns (domain, ports, adapters, CLI)\n- Comprehensive error handling with semantic failure classes\n- Atomic durability guarantees for critical state\n- Extensibility through port-based design\n- Full test coverage for implemented features\n- Deterministic, testable behavior (via stub backend)\n\nThe implementation is **ready for the next layer: retry/remediation logic** which would consume the failure classes and orchestrate re-execution of failed stages."}],"totalDurationMs":99090,"totalTokens":72292,"totalToolUseCount":30,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2974,"cache_read_input_tokens":64728,"output_tokens":4586,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2974},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
